title: For Sale/Trade:  Century AK-74, 5.45X39
postcontent:
I have a Polish AK-74 in 5.45X39 cal in excellent condition. This is the caliber the Russians switched to in 1974.  They found it vastly superior to the the 7.62X39, they used to use.  (They never switched back).  

   This caliber extends the effective range by several hundred meters.  It has high velocity, much flatter trajectory, better accuracy, and almost NO recoil.  It has a reputation as a much better "stopper".  Afgan fighters feared it, and called it the "Poison bullet".

   Ammo is the cheapest center fire you can by.  (1080 rds in sealed cans for $139.)

   Rifle comes with a side folding, military issue, metal butt stock. (It can be fired with stock folded.)  Tapco trigger is EXCELLENT!  This model has safety access on BOTH side of receiver.  Forearm has high quality rails on top, both sides, and bottom.   Red dot, laser, light and vertical grip can be easily mounted.  Two 30 rd mags included.

   This is the one you want when it all hits the fan!!!

title: For Sale:  Walther model 4       .32 cal
postcontent:
I have for sale a Walther Model 4 for sale. It is a 
Third Variant (Post-war production, approximately 1920-1923.)  The Model 4 is a relatively simple handgun of blowback design, with a fixed barrel, an external extractor, and a concealed hammer.  Its most unusual feature is that (like its predecessor the Model 3) its extractor and ejection port are on the left.  The barrel acts as a guide for the concentric recoil spring, which is held in place by a bayonette-type lug that covers the front of the barrel, and by a sleeve at the rear which also serves to cover the spring. When the slide moves rearward, it forces the trigger bar down, disconnecting it from the sear.  The safety is a rotating thumb lever that positively locks the cocked hammer.  There is a screw on the backstrap of the grip that regulates the tension of the flat hammer spring. The gun is well-balanced, fits the hand very nicely, and points instinctively.  It is also reasonably accurate.
